notesStmt.note: Shemu᾿el ben Mosheh de Medina (b. 1505, d. 1589), Talmudist from Salonica: inscribed with his name in a purchase note (folio 1r).
Giovanni Domenico Carretto, Italian censor (active1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1618 (folio 477v); 100-101 & app. 80-84.
Birth entries in Spanish of four sons of an unknown family, 1699, 1700, 1702, 1704 (folio 1r).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The so-called 'Duke of Sussex Bible' with vowel-points and accents, accompanied by masorah magna and parva.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 45; written lines: 44; Uniform layout. Ruling visible at times. Flesh side and hair side distinguishable. The masorah magna occupies two lines at the top of the page and three at the bottom of the page. In the lower margin it is written in the form of ornamental patterns (micrography). Gilt edges.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi square script, punctuated, of the second half of the 14th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Biblia Hebraica. Mus. Brit. Jure Emptionis. 15,252. Plut.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Prince Augustus Frederick (b. 1773, d. 1843), duke of Sussex: his sale 31 July 1844, lot 103: inscribed (folio 478v), purchased by the British Museum through Thomas Rodd the younger (b. 1796, d. 1849), for £5.
